  Setup:
  - "Place Active Event: \nPlace cards \n#50 Army of the West, \n#51 Death of Henry
    Linn Dodge, \n#53 Manuelito\u2019s War, and \n#54 The American Civil War face-up
    along the bottom edge of the map. \nThey are in-play."
  - "Place Starting Families In Play: \nA, B, C, D, & E (Ferocity 0) in any Area
    of Shiprock, San Juan Valley, Zuni Mountains, Hopi Land and Canyon de Chelly.
    \nPlace all remaining Family Counters into the holding spaces of each Family
    Box. "
  - "Next, place any two counters into each Family\u2019s Family Box. \nTo determine
    which population counter is not placed, roll a die for each family and consult
    the numeric values placed over the population counter spaces. \nPlace the Manuelito
    counter with any on-map Family."
  - "Place Starting Elders In Play: \nPlace 1 elder counter into each of the 3 leftmost
    boxes of the Elder Display."
  - "Place Drought Counters: \nPlace 1 drought counter into each Territory."
  - "Subjugation of New Mexico: \nNo cubes."
  - "Prepare Draw Cups: \nPlace all Corn counters into a clean empty container from
    which they can be drawn during play. Do the same with the Intruder counters."
  - "Prepare Raid Pool: \nPrepare the Raid Pool by placing 3 red, 3 black, 4 brown,
    4 white, 2 yellow, 1 green, and 1 blue cube into the draw bag; return all other
    cubes to the game box."
  - "Prepare Cultural Development Cards: \nSelect 1 set of 3 Cultural Development
    Cards to be available for use in the game. \nCollect the remaining 7 Level 1
    Cultural Development Cards and shuffle them. \nDraw three Cultural Development
    Cards and set them along with the Level 2 and 3 cards from their set back into
    the box."
  - "General Records Track: \nMilitary Points: 5 \nEnemy Ferocity: 5 \nCulture Points:
    5 \nDin\xE9 APs: 0 \nMorale: 5"
  - "Remove Trade Goods & Harass Counters: \nSet 6 Trade Goods and 2 Harass counters
    off to the side. They are neither in play, nor available. They become available
    when a Weaving or the Masters of the Mesas Level 2 Cultural Development Card
    is purchased."
  - "Set Up Resources: \nPlace 4 Horse, 4 Sheep and 1 Firearms counter into the Resources
    Box. \nPlace all remaining Population and animal counters in the Out of Play
    Box."
  - "Set Up Enemy Instruction Display: \nPlace all American (blue) Instruction counters
    into a cup. \nDraw counters randomly from this cup one at a time and place into
    an empty space on the Enemy Instruction Display. Fill Active column first from
    top to bottom, then the Standby column from top to bottom."
  - "Set Up Enemy Pieces: \nPlace a Fort in Area #1 of Zuni Mountains and Hopi Land.
    \nPlace one Rancho Outpost counter into Area #1 of Shiprock and San Juan Valley.
    \nPlace all remaining Rancho Outpost counters, Enemy AP counters, and Tribal
    Raid counters in the Enemy Out of Play box."
  - "Collect Starting Cultural Development Card: \nCollect and put into play four
    of the five remaining sets of Cultural Development Cards. \nReturn the one of
    the five sets to the box; these three cards will not be used in the game."
  - "Note Victory Conditions: \nIf the game does not end beforehand, determine victory
    or defeat after card #55 Kit Carson is resolved. \nFor each black cube in Subjugation
    of New Mexico box, add +1 Enemy Morale. \nNext, subtract the number of Enemy
    Morale from Military Points and compare the difference on the table on the next
    screen. "
  - "Major Victory: Military Pts > Enemy Morale\r\nMinor Victory: 1+ Military Pt
    and Military Pts = Enemy Morale \r\nMinor Defeat:  1+ Military Pt and Military
    Pts < Enemy Morale [Historical] \r\nMinor Defeat:  0 Military Pts and 0 Enemy
    Morale \r\nMajor Defeat:  0 Military Pts and 1+ Enemy Morale"
  - "To prepare the deck for this scenario: \n1. Shuffle all Operations Cards (no
    Ceremony Cards). \n2. Deal 3 Operations Cards face-down to form the bottom of
    the deck. \n3.Shuffle Transitional Event Card #55 Rope Thrower: Kit Carson into
    these 3 cards. "
  - "4. Deal 5 more Operations Cards face-down on top of the deck. DO NOT LOOK AT
    REMAINING OPERATIONS CARDS; PUT THEM BACK INTO THE BOX! \n5. Shuffle all 12 Ceremony
    Cards. "
  - 6. Draw 1 Ceremony Card and add 1 population counter to the Passage of Time Box
    as directed by Ceremony Card step 3. If you have no cards in hand, you may take
    the card into his hand as directed by the Ceremony Card step 3, otherwise discard
    the card. If there are < 3 population counters in the Passage of Time box, repeat
    this step. Ignore Enemy Way Effects.
  - END
